<recipe>
	<name>Southern Pecan Pie</name>
	<yield_measure>Servings</yield_measure>
	<notes>Southern-style Pecan Pie is the thing I like second-most in the world.  Sweet Potato Pecan Pie is number one,  but this  isn't a recipe for that, is it now?  Hush and be happy.</notes>
	<ingredients>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>3</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>eggs</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>white Karo syrup</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>sugar</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>vanilla</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>2 Tbl</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>oleo</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1/8 tsp</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>salt</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>chopped pecans</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>unbaked 19" pie shell</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
	</ingredients>
	<preparation>Beat eggs slightly.  Mix in white syrup, sugar, oleo, vanilla and salt. Add pecans.  Bake at 400F for 15 minutes and at 350F for 30 to 35 minutes.

**I think Oleo = Margarine for us Yankees, close enough.
</preparation>
